        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> /shrug - maybe I'm wrong about what people expect on PvP, but it seems to me that there's a double standard on these servers.  On the one hand you have 'the anarchists' who take everything to extremes because they can, and on the other you have people who are trying to PvP with a sense of fair play.  Who's in the majority?  Who knows.  Maybe the second option is misguided, but there's no way these people can practice that kind of PvP with the first type going on.  In that sense the anarchistic mentality is abusive.  What should be done about it?  Well this environment is a relatively new one and I'm sure it's pretty tough to always see how people will use it to advantage.  I'm sure games in the future will split off that will better serve each interest.  In the meantime, if that's what spins your prop go for it - I'll stick to Prexus :)</P><P><BR>Takilth Shadowpath<BR>Iksar Warlock of the Final Shedding<BR>proud member of Shining Alliance<BR>Prexus</font></td>
